<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="738" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.00/447.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 37.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received and read with
                            interest your despatch No. 53, of October 12, 1912, with reference to
                            certain recent disturbances that occurred in Monrovia, and in reply
                            informs you that the attitude taken by you in the matter has the
                            Department’s approval.* * *</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>